Free and voluntary vaccination against pneumococcal disease
Immunization against pneumococcal changes the usual from January.
It is the first to be free and voluntary for families.
But even now, voices are saying that the mandatory vaccination would be more effective.
Preparations for the introduction of the free pneumococcal vaccine culminate.
The Institute of Medicine already sets the maximum prices for the vaccines that the health insurance companies have to pay.
