Under Spanish law, a vehicle whose chassis number has been deregistered may no longer drive on the roads, but certain undamaged parts may be used as spare parts.
On the other hand, cars with a historical value may be allowed again, even if they have been unregistered after difficult government procedures.
Cost estimate of the workshop in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, the company Audatex ensures that the user receives a cost estimate in just four steps: identification of the vehicle, search for the spare part, creation and creation of a cost estimate.
The easy handling of these systems is a fundamental condition, especially in order to convince the older professionals who are usually more or less against the use of these new computer techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are passenger cars, 109 off-road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, you need a computer with an internet connection to use it.
After the model to be repaired has been identified using the chassis number, a graphic of the respective model appears and then the required spare part is selected.
The user can include variables, such as the price for the working hours, surcharges or discounts and after that he can have the cost estimate printed and passed on to his customers.
However, AudaTaller is not a review tool like AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalog.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop does not include estimated working hours.
The cost of using this tool is 350 euros per year, an amount that the customer can immediately pay.
At the moment, the company Audatex is working on offering these images in three-dimensional format.
This is an innovation that car mechanics have been waiting for for a long time, since you can choose a door with it, for example, and then turn the picture completely to look at the inside.
